+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CqB8j975XqA49UCEM8biLX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consensus isn't available (no API keys). I'll proceed with autopilot mode, making decisions myself based on the requirements. Let me design the architecture directly.\n\nStarting autopilot. I'll narrate each decision and proceed through the design.\n\n**Q1: Core class architecture?**\n→ Choosing: **Option B - Separate classes with orchestrator**\n  Reasoning: A `TaskQueueSystem` orchestrator manages named `Queue` instances. Each `Queue` handles its own pending tasks, concurrency, middleware, and DLQ. `Task` is a standalone model. `Scheduler` handles recurring tasks. This separates concerns cleanly while keeping interactions manageable.\n\n**Q2: Task data model?**\n→ Choosing: Comprehensive Task interface with all fields from the start, using `crypto.randomUUID()` for IDs.\n  Reasoning: Building all fields upfront avoids retrofitting. UUID gives true uniqueness. Optional fields keep Phase 1 simple.\n\n**Q3: Data structure for pending tasks?**\n→ Choosing: **Option A - Sorted array with insertion sort**\n  Reasoning: For moderate queue sizes, a sorted array with binary search insertion is simple, gives O(log n) insert via `findIndex` + `splice`, and O(n) retrieval (scanning for first available). The simplicity outweighs the minor perf cost. Filtering for delays and dependencies requires scanning anyway.\n\n**Q4: Event/notification system?**\n→ Choosing: Simple EventEmitter pattern for progress notifications and internal coordination.\n  Reasoning: Phase 9 needs progress subscriptions, Phase 7 needs dependency resolution notifications. A lightweight typed event emitter covers both.\n\nLet me now write the full design document and then implement."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1508,"cache_read_input_tokens":26619,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1508},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aee493ec-91df-4b3e-8021-5d8430142283","uuid":"4dcf2dd8-6acb-41a1-bbe8-4e9961774b2f"}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CqB8j975XqA49UCEM8biLX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QCWg834NXdhkZyoTLtsH5P","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-task-queue-design.md","content":"# Task Queue System Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Core Classes\n- **TaskQueueSystem**: Main entry point / orchestrator. Manages named queues, global task registry, schedules, shutdown state.\n- **Queue**: Single named queue. Manages pending tasks (sorted array), processing set, DLQ, concurrency limits, middleware stack.\n- **Task**: Data model class with all lifecycle fields.\n- **Scheduler**: Manages recurring task schedules, cron parsing, tick mechanism.\n\n### Task States\n```\npending → processing → completed\n                    → failed (→ retry as pending, or → dead-lettered)\npending → cancelled\nprocessing → cancelled\nblocked (dependencies) → pending (when deps resolve)\ndelayed → pending (when availableAt passes)\n```\n\nActual enum: `pending | processing | completed | failed | cancelled`\nTasks can also be `delayed` (pending but not yet available) and `blocked` (pending but dependencies unmet) - these are sub-states of pending tracked via fields, not separate status values.\n\n### Task Model\n```typescript\ninterface Task {\n  id: string;                    // crypto.randomUUID()\n  status: TaskStatus;\n  payload: unknown;\n  queueName: string;\n  priority: number;              // 1-10, default 5\n  createdAt: Date;\n  updatedAt: Date;\n\n  // Delay\n  availableAt: Date | null;      // null = immediately available\n  delay?: number;                // original delay in ms\n\n  // Retry\n  attempts: number;              // how many times attempted\n  maxRetries: number;            // default 3\n  backoffDelay: number;          // default 1000ms\n  errors: Error[];               // error history\n\n  // Dependencies\n  dependencies: string[];        // task IDs that must complete first\n\n  // Progress\n  progress: number;              // 0-100\n  progressMessage?: string;\n\n  // Metadata\n  scheduledBy?: string;          // schedule ID if from recurring\n}\n```\n\n### Pending Task Storage\nSorted array per queue, ordered by: (priority ASC, availableAt ASC, createdAt ASC).\nOn retrieval, scan from front for first task that is:\n1. Available (availableAt <= now or null)\n2. Not blocked (all dependencies completed)\n3. Queue not at concurrency limit\n\n### API Surface\n```typescript\nclass TaskQueueSystem {\n  // Phase 1: Basic queue\n  addTask(payload, options?): Task\n  getNextTask(queueName?): Task | null\n  getTaskCount(queueName?): number\n  getTask(taskId): Task | null\n\n  // Phase 2: Named queues\n  getQueueNames(): string[]\n\n  // Phase 5: Complete/fail\n  completeTask(taskId): void\n  failTask(taskId, error): void\n\n  // Phase 6: DLQ\n  getDeadLetterTasks(queueName?): Task[]\n  retryDeadLetterTask(taskId): Task\n  clearDeadLetterQueue(queueName?): void\n\n  // Phase 8: Concurrency\n  setConcurrency(queueName, limit): void\n  getConcurrency(queueName): { limit, active }\n\n  // Phase 9: Progress/cancel\n  updateProgress(taskId, progress, message?): void\n  onProgress(taskId, callback): () => void  // returns unsubscribe\n  cancelTask(taskId): void\n\n  // Phase 10: Recurring\n  addSchedule(id, cronExpr, queueName, payload, options?): Schedule\n  removeSchedule(id): void\n  getSchedules(): Schedule[]\n  tick(): Task[]\n\n  // Phase 11: Middleware\n  use(queueName, middleware): void\n  process(queueName, handler): void\n\n  // Phase 12: Shutdown\n  shutdown(options?): Promise<ShutdownResult>\n  onShutdown(callback): void\n}\n```\n\n### Cron Parsing (Phase 10)\nSimple parser supporting:\n- `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n- `0 * * * *` - hourly\n- `0 0 * * *` - daily at midnight\n\nParse into { minute, hour, dom, month, dow } with support for *, */N, and specific values.\n\n### Middleware (Phase 11)\n```typescript\ntype Middleware = (task: Task, next: () => Promise<void>) => Promise<void>;\n```\nMiddleware chain is built as nested function calls. Each queue has ordered middleware array + handler.\n\n### Shutdown (Phase 12)\nSets `isShuttingDown` flag. Returns promise that resolves when all processing tasks complete or timeout. Force-cancels remaining after timeout.\n\n## File Structure\n```\nsrc/\n  index.ts          - exports TaskQueueSystem and types\n  task-queue-system.ts - main orchestrator\n  queue.ts          - single queue implementation\n  task.ts           - task model\n  scheduler.ts      - recurring task scheduling\n  cron.ts           - cron expression parser\n  types.ts          - shared types and interfaces\n```\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1508,"cache_read_input_tokens":26619,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1508},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aee493ec-91df-4b3e-8021-5d8430142283","uuid":"4a57672d-6f4f-4115-a0e8-4f519bf0de64"}
+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QCWg834NXdhkZyoTLtsH5P","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-task-queue-design.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aee493ec-91df-4b3e-8021-5d8430142283","uuid":"f9c0d3dd-bfc4-47dc-bd6d-679b19889e20","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-task-queue-design.md","content":"# Task Queue System Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Core Classes\n- **TaskQueueSystem**: Main entry point / orchestrator. Manages named queues, global task registry, schedules, shutdown state.\n- **Queue**: Single named queue. Manages pending tasks (sorted array), processing set, DLQ, concurrency limits, middleware stack.\n- **Task**: Data model class with all lifecycle fields.\n- **Scheduler**: Manages recurring task schedules, cron parsing, tick mechanism.\n\n### Task States\n```\npending → processing → completed\n                    → failed (→ retry as pending, or → dead-lettered)\npending → cancelled\nprocessing → cancelled\nblocked (dependencies) → pending (when deps resolve)\ndelayed → pending (when availableAt passes)\n```\n\nActual enum: `pending | processing | completed | failed | cancelled`\nTasks can also be `delayed` (pending but not yet available) and `blocked` (pending but dependencies unmet) - these are sub-states of pending tracked via fields, not separate status values.\n\n### Task Model\n```typescript\ninterface Task {\n  id: string;                    // crypto.randomUUID()\n  status: TaskStatus;\n  payload: unknown;\n  queueName: string;\n  priority: number;              // 1-10, default 5\n  createdAt: Date;\n  updatedAt: Date;\n\n  // Delay\n  availableAt: Date | null;      // null = immediately available\n  delay?: number;                // original delay in ms\n\n  // Retry\n  attempts: number;              // how many times attempted\n  maxRetries: number;            // default 3\n  backoffDelay: number;          // default 1000ms\n  errors: Error[];               // error history\n\n  // Dependencies\n  dependencies: string[];        // task IDs that must complete first\n\n  // Progress\n  progress: number;              // 0-100\n  progressMessage?: string;\n\n  // Metadata\n  scheduledBy?: string;          // schedule ID if from recurring\n}\n```\n\n### Pending Task Storage\nSorted array per queue, ordered by: (priority ASC, availableAt ASC, createdAt ASC).\nOn retrieval, scan from front for first task that is:\n1. Available (availableAt <= now or null)\n2. Not blocked (all dependencies completed)\n3. Queue not at concurrency limit\n\n### API Surface\n```typescript\nclass TaskQueueSystem {\n  // Phase 1: Basic queue\n  addTask(payload, options?): Task\n  getNextTask(queueName?): Task | null\n  getTaskCount(queueName?): number\n  getTask(taskId): Task | null\n\n  // Phase 2: Named queues\n  getQueueNames(): string[]\n\n  // Phase 5: Complete/fail\n  completeTask(taskId): void\n  failTask(taskId, error): void\n\n  // Phase 6: DLQ\n  getDeadLetterTasks(queueName?): Task[]\n  retryDeadLetterTask(taskId): Task\n  clearDeadLetterQueue(queueName?): void\n\n  // Phase 8: Concurrency\n  setConcurrency(queueName, limit): void\n  getConcurrency(queueName): { limit, active }\n\n  // Phase 9: Progress/cancel\n  updateProgress(taskId, progress, message?): void\n  onProgress(taskId, callback): () => void  // returns unsubscribe\n  cancelTask(taskId): void\n\n  // Phase 10: Recurring\n  addSchedule(id, cronExpr, queueName, payload, options?): Schedule\n  removeSchedule(id): void\n  getSchedules(): Schedule[]\n  tick(): Task[]\n\n  // Phase 11: Middleware\n  use(queueName, middleware): void\n  process(queueName, handler): void\n\n  // Phase 12: Shutdown\n  shutdown(options?): Promise<ShutdownResult>\n  onShutdown(callback): void\n}\n```\n\n### Cron Parsing (Phase 10)\nSimple parser supporting:\n- `*/N * * * *` - every N minutes\n- `0 * * * *` - hourly\n- `0 0 * * *` - daily at midnight\n\nParse into { minute, hour, dom, month, dow } with support for *, */N, and specific values.\n\n### Middleware (Phase 11)\n```typescript\ntype Middleware = (task: Task, next: () => Promise<void>) => Promise<void>;\n```\nMiddleware chain is built as nested function calls. Each queue has ordered middleware array + handler.\n\n### Shutdown (Phase 12)\nSets `isShuttingDown` flag. Returns promise that resolves when all processing tasks complete or timeout. Force-cancels remaining after timeout.\n\n## File Structure\n```\nsrc/\n  index.ts          - exports TaskQueueSystem and types\n  task-queue-system.ts - main orchestrator\n  queue.ts          - single queue implementation\n  task.ts           - task model\n  scheduler.ts      - recurring task scheduling\n  cron.ts           - cron expression parser\n  types.ts          - shared types and interfaces\n```\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
