+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KpzwvfmGpC4fJd5SkwJnbj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me do a final review check - re-read each phase requirement and make sure I haven't missed anything. Let me verify a few specific edge cases:\n\n1. Phase 5 says \"baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)\" - let me verify my backoff formula matches.\n\nIn `queue.ts:101`: `const delay = task.backoffDelay * Math.pow(2, task.attempts - 1);`\n\nWhen task.attempts is 1 (first failure): delay = base * 2^0 = base * 1 = 1000ms\nWhen task.attempts is 2 (second failure): delay = base * 2^1 = base * 2 = 2000ms\nWhen task.attempts is 3: delay = base * 2^2 = base * 4 = 4000ms\n\nThat matches the spec: \"1s, 2s, 4s, ...\"\n\n2. Phase 6 says \"count of how many times they failed\" - the errors array tracks this.\n\n3. Phase 7 circular dependency detection - I need to make sure this actually works. The `detectCircularDependencies` method traverses from the dependencies of the new task's dependencies, looking for the new task's ID. But the new task hasn't been added yet at that point (it's added after validation). So a direct circular dependency (A depends on B, B depends on A) would work:\n   - Add A (no deps) → OK\n   - Add B (depends on A) → Check: traverse A's deps (none) → no cycle → OK\n   - Add C (depends on B, and let's say B depends on C) → But B doesn't depend on C at creation time since C doesn't exist yet\n\nActually, circular deps can only occur with the already-existing tasks' dep chains. Since we only add dependencies at creation time and can't modify them later, a true circular dependency would require task X to depend on task Y which depends on task X, but task X would already need to exist when creating Y, and Y would need to exist when creating X. So circular dependencies are only possible if there's a chain that leads back. The detection works correctly.\n\nLet me add a few more edge case tests to increase coverage:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":451,"cache_read_input_tokens":70076,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":451},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aee493ec-91df-4b3e-8021-5d8430142283","uuid":"a087eb82-379e-4335-9734-d9505fa2524a"}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KpzwvfmGpC4fJd5SkwJnbj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LHJ8V1v6oyE4pRJyjiqe4E","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/tests/integration.test.ts","content":"import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { TaskQueueSystem } from '../src/index.js';\n\ndescribe('Integration: Cross-phase interactions', () => {\n  let tqs: TaskQueueSystem;\n\n  beforeEach(() => {\n    tqs = new TaskQueueSystem();\n  });\n\n  it('should handle priority + delay + dependencies together', () => {\n    // Create a dependency chain with priorities and delays\n    const dep = tqs.addTask('dependency', { priority: 5 });\n    const blocked = tqs.addTask('blocked-high-priority', {\n      priority: 1,\n      dependencies: [dep.id],\n    });\n    tqs.addTask('available-low-priority', { priority: 10 });\n\n    // dep should come first (priority 5, available)\n    // blocked has priority 1 but is blocked\n    // available has priority 10, so it comes after dep\n    const first = tqs.getNextTask();\n    expect(first?.payload).toBe('dependency');\n\n    const second = tqs.getNextTask();\n    expect(second?.payload).toBe('available-low-priority');\n\n    // blocked is still blocked\n    expect(tqs.getNextTask()).toBeNull();\n\n    // Complete dependency\n    tqs.completeTask(dep.id);\n\n    // Now blocked should be available\n    const third = tqs.getNextTask();\n    expect(third?.payload).toBe('blocked-high-priority');\n    expect(third?.id).toBe(blocked.id);\n  });\n\n  it('should handle retry + concurrency interaction', () => {\n    tqs.setConcurrency('default', 1);\n    const task = tqs.addTask('retry-me', { maxRetries: 2, backoffDelay: 10 });\n    tqs.addTask('waiting');\n\n    // Process first task\n    const t = tqs.getNextTask();\n    expect(t?.id).toBe(task.id);\n\n    // Concurrency blocks second task\n    expect(tqs.getNextTask()).toBeNull();\n\n    // Fail first task - should retry\n    tqs.failTask(task.id, 'err');\n    task.availableAt = new Date(Date.now() - 1); // Make it available\n\n    // Concurrency slot should be free now\n    const next = tqs.getNextTask();\n    expect(next).not.toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('should handle middleware + retry interaction', async () => {\n    let callCount = 0;\n\n    tqs.use('default', async (task, next) => {\n      callCount++;\n      await next();\n    });\n\n    tqs.process('default', async () => {\n      if (callCount === 1) {\n        throw new Error('first attempt fails');\n      }\n    });\n\n    const task = tqs.addTask('retry-via-middleware', { maxRetries: 2, backoffDelay: 10 });\n    await tqs.processNext();\n\n    // Task should have been retried (failed on first attempt)\n    expect(task.status).toBe('pending');\n    expect(callCount).toBe(1);\n\n    // Make retry available\n    task.availableAt = new Date(Date.now() - 1);\n    await tqs.processNext();\n\n    // Second attempt should succeed\n    expect(task.status).toBe('completed');\n    expect(callCount).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('should handle cancel + concurrency - free slot on cancel', () => {\n    tqs.setConcurrency('default', 1);\n    const task = tqs.addTask('will-cancel');\n    tqs.addTask('waiting');\n\n    tqs.getNextTask();\n    expect(tqs.getNextTask()).toBeNull();\n\n    tqs.cancelTask(task.id);\n\n    // Slot should be free\n    const next = tqs.getNextTask();\n    expect(next?.payload).toBe('waiting');\n  });\n\n  it('should handle progress + cancel interaction', () => {\n    const task = tqs.addTask('test');\n    tqs.getNextTask();\n\n    tqs.updateProgress(task.id, 50, 'halfway');\n    tqs.cancelTask(task.id);\n\n    expect(task.status).toBe('cancelled');\n    expect(task.progress).toBe(50); // Progress preserved\n  });\n\n  it('should track DLQ task error count correctly through retries', () => {\n    const task = tqs.addTask('doomed', { maxRetries: 2, backoffDelay: 10 });\n\n    // First attempt\n    tqs.getNextTask();\n    tqs.failTask(task.id, 'err1');\n    expect(task.errors.length).toBe(1);\n\n    // Second attempt\n    task.availableAt = new Date(Date.now() - 1);\n    tqs.getNextTask();\n    tqs.failTask(task.id, 'err2');\n\n    // Now in DLQ\n    expect(task.status).toBe('failed');\n    expect(task.errors.length).toBe(2);\n    expect(task.attempts).toBe(2);\n\n    const dlq = tqs.getDeadLetterTasks();\n    expect(dlq.length).toBe(1);\n    expect(dlq[0].errors.length).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('should handle schedule + middleware interaction', async () => {\n    const processed: string[] = [];\n\n    tqs.use('default', async (task, next) => {\n      processed.push(task.payload as string);\n      await next();\n    });\n\n    tqs.process('default', async () => {\n      // handler\n    });\n\n    tqs.addSchedule('s1', '*/5 * * * *', 'default', 'scheduled-payload');\n\n    const now = new Date();\n    now.setMinutes(10, 0, 0);\n    const tasks = tqs.tick(now);\n    expect(tasks.length).toBe(1);\n\n    await tqs.processNext();\n    expect(processed).toEqual(['scheduled-payload']);\n  });\n\n  it('should prevent adding tasks during shutdown', async () => {\n    const shutdownPromise = tqs.shutdown();\n    expect(() => tqs.addTask('nope')).toThrow(/shutting down/);\n    await shutdownPromise;\n  });\n\n  it('should handle empty queues gracefully everywhere', () => {\n    expect(tqs.getNextTask()).toBeNull();\n    expect(tqs.getNextTask('nonexistent')).toBeNull();\n    expect(tqs.getTaskCount()).toBe(0);\n    expect(tqs.getTaskCount('nonexistent')).toBe(0);\n    expect(tqs.getQueueNames()).toEqual([]);\n    expect(tqs.getDeadLetterTasks()).toEqual([]);\n    expect(tqs.getDeadLetterTasks('nonexistent')).toEqual([]);\n  });\n});\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":451,"cache_read_input_tokens":70076,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_inp